article.headline: Southern Utah 84, Chicago State 66
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Justin Allen and Marcus Carson scored 15 points each, leading Southern Utah to an 84-66 win over Chicago State on Thursday night. Orlando Griego scored 12 points for the Thunderbirds (9-5), who remain unbeaten at home. Swaney Cooper and Steve Barnes added 11 points each, and Barnes had eight assists. Southern Utah shot 71 percent from the field in the first half and 64 percent overall. Royce Parran led Chicago State (5-11) with 22 points, while John Cantrell scored 19 points and Kourtney Calvin added 14. The Cougars forced 19 turnovers and came up with 12 steals, including four by Cantrell. The Thunderbirds trailed 2-0 before staging a 15-3 run that gave them the lead for good. David Marek's three-point play gave Southern Utah its biggest lead, 36-16, with 6:07 to go in the first half. Parran brought the Cougars back within eight points, 54-46, with a 3-pointer from the left wing with 12:58 to play. But Cooper made a three-point play and followed with a jump hook in the key, after which Griego nailed a 3-pointer from the top of the key, giving the Thunderbirds a 62-46 lead with 11:06 left. Chicago State couldn't reduce the deficit below 11 points after that. The Cougars played without head coach Kevin Jones, who sat out as a result of an incident involving members of the men's basketball team, according to a statement from Chicago State. Assistant coach Jason Kent served as head coach.
